     "fermionic Gaussian state", "fermionic quantum computation"}, 
    "specialkeywords" -> {}, "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True,
     "label" -> "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "WickProjection[ws, {k1, k2, ...} -> {s1, s2, ...}] applies the \
projection 1 - n Subscript[k, j] or n Subscript[k, j] on the Wick state ws \
depending on the occupation sj = 0 or sj = 1, respectively, of the bare \
fermion mode kj. WickProjection[ws, mat -> {s1, s2, ..., sm}] applies the \
projection for the dressed fermion modes described by m*n row-orthogonal \
isometric matrix (mat . mat^\\[Dagger] = I), where n is the total number of \
bare modes.", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> 
    "WickProjection", "titlemodifier" -> "", "metadescription" -> "", 
